# CholecTrack20 Dataset (Usage in This Project)

This project uses the **CholecTrack20** dataset, introduced by Nwoye et al. at CVPR 2025.
The dataset provides **20 annotated laparoscopic cholecystectomy videos** with tool tracking labels, designed for multi-perspective surgical instrument trajectory analysis.

---

## ðŸ“Œ Dataset Overview
- **Procedures**: Laparoscopic cholecystectomy
- **Videos**: 20 anonymized surgical videos
- **Annotations**:
  - Tool bounding boxes (7 categories: grasper, bipolar, hook, scissors, clipper, irrigator, specimen bag)
  - Operator identities (main surgeon, assistant, null)
  - Phase labels and visual conditions (occlusion, smoke, bleeding, blur)
  - Multi-perspective tracking:
    1. **Visibility trajectory** (in camera view)
    2. **Intracorporeal trajectory** (inside patientâ€™s body)
    3. **Intraoperative trajectory** (entire procedure, OOCV & OOB handled)

- **Frame rate**: 1 FPS annotations (~35k frames, ~65k labeled instances);
  raw videos available at 25 FPS for inference.

---

## ðŸ“‚ Data Access
Due to storage limits, **the full dataset is not included in this repository**.
You can download it from the official sources:

- [Official Website (Camma Lab)](https://camma.u-strasbg.fr/datasets/cholectrack20/)
- [ArXiv Paper (with links)](https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.07352)

---

